==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Chlorhydrin
<hw>Chlor`hy"drin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>One of a class of compounds formed from certain polybasic alcohols
(and especially glycerin) by the substitution of chlorine for one or
more hydroxyl groups.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chloric</ent>⟦br⟧
